summary: In this context, propane-1,2-diol (also known as propylene glycol) and 1-propanol are both mentioned as components detected in the chemical analysis of silage samples. They are analyzed using gas chromatography (GC) alongside other compounds like lactic acid and ethanol. However, there is no direct discussion of their relationship or interaction within the context provided, indicating they are simply part of the same analytical procedure without further relevance to each other.
